p;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;QA, Documentation &amp;amp; Data Governance&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Build and maintain a rigorous QA process including automated validation checks, data reconciliation protocols, and regression testing before anything reaches a stakeholder&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Develop and maintain comprehensive documentation for all reporting assets — data dictionaries, calculation logic, source-to-dashboard lineage, and refresh schedules&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Partner with Revenue Systems and Data Engineering to define data architecture requirements and advocate for upstream data quality from Salesforce, marketing automation, and other GTM sources&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;AI &amp;amp; Innovation&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Champion adoption of AI-powered analytics tools — AI-assisted data exploration, automated insight generation, natural language querying — to accelerate how the GTM org di

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a skilled and driven &lt;strong&gt;Revenue Operations Partner II&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Revenue Operations &amp;amp; Strategy team. In this role, you’ll partner closely with Sales, Marketing, and other go-to-market teams to drive alignment, optimize processes, and support data-driven decision-making. You’ll play a key role in ensuring operational efficiency across the revenue cycle, leveraging insights and systems expertise to enhance forecasting accuracy, workflow consistency, and overall performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Cross-Functional Alignment:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with Sales and Marketing to ensure cohesive strategies and seamless handoffs across the customer journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimize Processes:&lt;/strong&gt; Evaluate and improve workflows across sales and marketing operations, identifying opportunities for automation and efficiency gains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyze and Report on Performance:&lt;/strong&gt; Track and interpret key revenue metrics from lead generation through close, providing actionable recommendations to improve outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support Forecasting and Planning:&lt;/strong&gt; Maintain and enhance forecasting processes to improve accuracy, visibility, and accountability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Implement and Enforce Best Practices:&lt;/strong&gt; Help standardize processes and ensure consistent use of tools and data across teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System and Tool Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Support Salesforce CPQ setup and maintenance, including product configuration, pricing rules, and quote templates.&lt;/p&gt;
